daniel wrote a review Dec 2019
Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia1 contribution
Excellent Stay
There are so much satisfaction to stay in this cozy place. We chose this place when we in Da Nang & we felt this is an excellent choice for both of us. Room is clean, staffs are all friendly & the location of this hotel is super convenient. If you manage to get the room with balcony, there is a plus point. Would like to hanks to a staff call Mya. She offer me a 10k dong as I finished my cash to enter the airport on last day. It makes my days for this little help. At last, the breakfast is awesome. Cooked by a pretty local aunty. Must spend the breakfast over Minh House. BRAVO
Haneya79 wrote a review Dec 2019
Singapore, Singapore49 contributions4 helpful votes
+1
Cozy House of Hospitality - a must visit
Exceptional hospitality from the time you step in till you check out, Ms Thu,Mya,Nhi & Kelvin were Amazing !! They were such amazing helpful Stars. The interior was like stepping into an oasis, cozy decor. Comfy beds, sweet aroma oil when you strip in. I wish,I had booked more extra nights here. It was so worth it! The rooms were neat, well equipped even with electric stoves & my room was pool access which was huge winner with my 7yr old. Morning breakfast was so my kind of quality over quantity. Good spread and eggs cooked to yr preference, Kelvin took a lot of care in the order & Also Emma the cook, her pho was so delish !! juices were also fresh. Location wise, very accessible to beach & Han market is literally 7mins by car/taxi. We even order grab food for dinner…
Lim T wrote a review Dec 2019
Brunei Darussalam2 contributions
Great Place
Cozy and beautiful place with friendly staff. Well maintained hotel with a clean swimming pool. Clean rooms with all the necessary amenities provided. Delicious breakfast which serve local food. Great place for friends and couples. The location is great as well with few minutes walk to the beach and most tourist attractions nearby.
Laurent K wrote a review Dec 2019
Mittelbergheim, France51 contributions6 helpful votes
Nice place, great value!
“Don’t judge a book by its cover!” This phrase definitely describe your arrival...located in a small street behind the main roads, the hotel welcomes you through a beautiful wooden double door. Definitely the team’s idea to have the main entrance closed for the reference of “family house”. When we arrived, the street was under refurbishment so quite bumpy. Upon your entry in the lobby, big smiles are welcoming you! I have never seen staff smiling that much... hospitality still means something in some places. We were then invited to seat down so the staff could provide us with all the relevant information for our stay. Minh House staffs are friendly and professional at the same time. Even though English is not their first language, they communicated without difficulty. As…
