Kelly S wrote a review Nov 2019
14 contributions1 helpful vote
Surprising Oasis in the Middle of Vietnam's Fast Developing City
Our group LOVED our stay at the Minh House! A surprising oasis in Da Nang- minutes walk from the ocean, street food, coffeeshops and souvenir shopping. My group was running late to an event and the staff met us at the entrance and offered to leave our things at the desk. They were always cheerful and accommodating. The rooms were pristine with water bottles, snacks and a view of the beautiful pool. The rain showers in the room, robes, and well lit sink areas were all among the highlights. We needed an extra bed in our room and they already had one there by the time we got in. The breakfast was wonderful- many local options to choose from. The day we left we had an early flight and the staff got up early to make us banh mi sandwiches and tea to eat before we went- at 6am! The…
Date of stay: November 2019
Him L wrote a review Nov 2019
11 contributions
Enjoyable stay, value for money
The boutique hotel is exactly what it looks like in the photos, very modern and stylish. Staff are extremely nice and always wear a smile. Breakfast was simple but tasty. A lovely chef who made good coffee! What I dislike though is the interior of room is quite old. Bed sheet, towels are quite grey and yellow. Checked the building was launched in 2016, couldn’t believe its aging that fast. Overall it’s a lovely stay- and value for money
Ian Pons wrote a review Nov 2019
Italian Riviera, Italy7 contributions
Happy hotel and feel like my house
The hotel was good. Great grab & go breakfast behind the lobby. Restaurant and swimming pool were nice too. Front desk people were courteous and checked us in quickly. Although the bed was too soft, all linens were clean. Excellent location. Very friendly staff, very clean. Had a great time would stay again.
